feat: heuristic guardrail + reframed competitive narrative

Two changes driven by hackathon-judging feedback: (1) a concrete
guardrail on the backend so the landing can honestly claim it (no
more "Roadmap"), (2) reframed messaging on the landing so DoorDash
goes from "benchmark we chase" to "prior art with yesterday's
architecture", emphasizing what Mise uniquely ships.

Backend

- New `backend/app/core/quality.py` — a heuristic guardrail that
  scores every pipeline run and returns a `QualitySignal` with
  status (ready / review_recommended / likely_failure), confidence,
  structured flags, and plain-language reasons. Seven checks cover
  the failure modes we actually hit during dev: low dish count,
  missing prices, missing categories, skeleton ingredients, price
  outliers (Iglewicz-Hoaglin MAD, robust to self-masking), near-
  duplicate canonicals (Jaccard), partial source failure.
- `pipeline._build_cockpit` now attaches the `QualitySignal` to
  every `CockpitState`.
- `/api/catalog/{run_id}.json` surfaces the `quality_signal` block
  at the document root so downstream systems can branch on it
  before indexing.
- `CockpitState.quality_signal` field added (domain model); circular
  import broken via `TYPE_CHECKING` in quality.py.
- Bella Italia fixture ships a `ready`-status signal so demo stays
  deterministic.
- Tests: `test_quality.py` exercises every flag branch;
  `test_catalog.py` pins the exported shape.

Frontend

- `domain/types.ts` mirrors `QualitySignal` and `QualityStatus`.
- New `QualitySignalPane` component — tone-aware badge (olive /
  amber / red) with reasons list and per-metric footer. Rendered
  above the metrics pane in the Cockpit.
- `MetricsPane` caption no longer leaks a `.py` path; reads
  "from the reproducible eval suite" instead.
- Landing `Compare` section: H2 rewritten to "The industry built
  menu pipelines before vision models were good enough." Intro
  paragraphs now frame DoorDash's OCR → LLM → guardrail → HITL
  stack as the prior generation (because LLMs couldn't read a
  photo directly until Opus 4.7).
- Comparison grid: every row now has an `unique: boolean` flag.
  When true, the row gets a subtle gold tint plus an "Only Mise"
  pill next to the capability name. Turns a flat "Yes/Yes/No"
  matrix into something that actually reads the story. Quality-
  signal row now documents Mise's heuristic guardrail (not
  roadmap).
- New plain-language intro above the JSON preview ("What Mise
  returns on the first call") so non-tech readers engage with it
  too.
- Only `.py` reference on the landing (`evals/run_eval.py`) replaced
  with prose.

Docs

- `docs/competitive_benchmark.md`: the DoorDash-benchmark section
  now shows ✅ for the guardrail row (with the honest caveat that
  Mise ships heuristics where DoorDash ships a trained LightGBM
  classifier) and describes the upgrade path.

Tests + build

- Backend: 67 tests green (11 new in test_quality.py plus the
  updated catalog test).
- Frontend: `tsc -b && vite build` clean.
EOF
